Create “ Age Group” Chart 15

Step 1:  Creating a Chart based on the previous Chart (Time Chart).

1.     Copy and paste " Time” Chart. Use Ctrl V to paste the chart.

2.     Delete the "Month, Year, Day, Holiday " From the shared axis 

3.     Drag and drop "Age Group " column to the shared axis 

Step 2: Configure the “Age Group” chart

         Click on the Format icon on the visualization bar

a.    General Tab

·         X- Position: 766

·         Y Position:  116

·         Width: 514

·         Height: 315

·         Legend: on

·         Position: Top

·         Title: OFF 

b.    Configure the X axis: ON

·         Keep the same format from the previous Chart (Time Chart). 

c.    Configure the Y- axis

1.    Y-axis Column

·         Position: Left

·         Scale type: Liner

·         Start: -10

·         End: 20

·         Keep the same format for the rest from the previous (time chart)

2.    Y- axis Line

·         Position: Right

·         Start: -0.1

·         End: Auto

·         Keep the same format the rest.

3.    Keep the same Format for Data Color, Data Label, Shape, Background and Boarder, Change only the title to “Age Group".



Follow the gif below to format the “Age Group” Chart
